title: TikTok agrees to deal to cede control of US business to American investor group
content: The deal closes a long-running drama in which U.S. authorities have sought to compel ByteDance to divest.

title: Apple becomes a debt collector with its new developer agreement
content: Apple says it can now collect any money a developer owes the tech giant at any time.

title: Instacart to pay $60M to settle FTC claims it deceived consumers
content: The federal agency alleged Instacart misled consumers with unlawful tactics, causing them to pay higher fees while also denying refunds.

title: ChatGPT launches an app store, lets developers know it’s open for business
content: OpenAI is looking to populate its flagship chatbot with a host of new user experiences.

title: Pickle Robot adds Tesla veteran as first CFO
content: Jeff Evanson recently joined Pickle Robot as the company's first CFO as the startup has allegedly expanded its partnership with UPS.

title: Why British politicians are flocking to American tech giants
content: Former British Chancellor of the Exchequer George Osborne has joined OpenAI as managing director and head of OpenAI for Countries. He also will run Coinbase's internal advisory council.

title: ChatGPT’s mobile app hits new milestone of $3B in consumer spending
content: ChatGPT has reached $3B in lifetime mobile consumer spending in just 31 months, faster than TikTok and major streaming apps.

title: LinkedIn’s profile verification push is accelerating — and India is leading the charge in 2025
content: LinkedIn profile verification adoption in India has risen about 80% in the past 12 months.

title: These startups are building innovations that make life (and death) better
content: Founders Gabriel Sanchez (Enspectra Health) and Tom Harries (Earth Funeral) share what it takes to build in heavily regulated industries where “move fast and break things” simply won’t work. title: These 21-year-old dropouts raised $2M to build Givefront, a fintech for nonprofits
content: YC-backed Givefront is building a fintech designed specifically for nonprofits, including food banks, churches, and homeowner associations.

title: Trump Media is merging with fusion power company TAE Technologies in $6B+ deal
content: The merger would broaden Trump Media’s holdings into the nascent fusion power space while data centers clamor for more electricity amid the ongoing AI boom.

title: TDK Ventures, Accel set to back India’s EtherealX in reusable launch vehicle push: Sources
content: EtherealX aims to take on SpaceX's Falcon 9 with its fully reusable rocket.

title: Tech provider for NHS England confirms data breach
content: U.K.-based healthcare tech provider DXS International said it discovered and contained a data breach on Sunday. A ransomware gang took credit for the breach.

title: Peripheral Labs taps into self-driving car sensors to bring sports fans right into the game
content: The startup has raised a $3.6 million seed round led by Khosla Ventures.
